a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Closers Copy is best suited for sales copy, landing pages, email sequences, conversion copywriting, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. NovelAI, meanwhile, shines for interactive fiction, storytelling, creative writing, roleplaying, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Closers Copy describes itself as \"AI copywriting tool built on proven sales frameworks.\" NovelAI, established in 2021, positions itself as \"AI storytelling tool with custom models trained on literature.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **NovelAI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Closers Copy is a poor choice — far from it. Closers Copy excels in its own right, particularly for sales copy and landing pages.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value custom ai models fine-tuned on published literature, go with NovelAI. If built on proven copywriting frameworks (aida, pas, etc.) matters more to you, Closers Copy is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
